# ── Dogfood / product control plane ──────────────────────────────────
# When Halo is instantiated on itself (World A = World B), `.halo/` is a
# local run state only. Other users clone a clean factory — never ship
# dogfood specs, evidence, loop counters, batons, or prompt history.
.halo/

# Generated product boot script at factory root during dogfood only.
# Product TARGETS keep their own init.sh; factory protocol is in docs/skills.
/init.sh

# Dogfood scaffold leftovers at factory root (existing profile health marker)
/halo-health.json

# Product-only config dropped into factory when dogfooding (templates live under templates/project/)
/HALO.md

# Progress / next-prompt leftovers if ever written outside .halo/
/progress.md
/claude-progress.txt

*.log
.idea/
.vscode/
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.coverage
htmlcov/
